### [Genesis Chapter 42](../../../bib/kjv/gen042.htm#001.md)

[Genesis](../../../bib/kjv/gen001.htm#001.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_000">gen 42:0</span></span>

Overview

[Gen 42:1](../../../bib/kjv/gen042.htm#001.md), Jacob sends his ten sons to
buy corn in Egypt; [Gen 42:16](../../../bib/kjv/gen042.htm#016.md), They
are imprisoned by Joseph for spies; [Gen
42:18](../../../bib/kjv/gen042.htm#018.md), They are set at liberty, on
condition to bring Benjamin; [Gen
42:21](../../../bib/kjv/gen042.htm#021.md), They have remorse for Joseph;
[Gen 42:24](../../../bib/kjv/gen042.htm#024.md), Simeon is kept for a
pledge; [Gen 42:25](../../../bib/kjv/gen042.htm#025.md), They return with
corn, and their money; [Gen 42:29](../../../bib/kjv/gen042.htm#029.md),
Their relation to Jacob; [Gen 42:36](../../../bib/kjv/gen042.htm#036.md),
Jacob refuses to send Benjamin.

